.TH QIFTOP\-AGENT 8 "2026-06-10" "qiftop 0.2.4" "System Administration"
.SH NAME
qiftop\-agent \- privileged D\-Bus agent exposing network statistics
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B qiftop\-agent
.RI [ options ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B qiftop\-agent
is the only qiftop component that touches the kernel. It runs as a
.B CAP_NET_ADMIN
daemon (normally as root under systemd), collects per\-interface counters
and per\-connection flows, and publishes them on D\-Bus as
.BR org.qiftop.NetworkAgent1 .
The unprivileged
.BR qiftop (1)
and
.BR nqiftop (1)
clients consume those signals so they never need privileges themselves.
.PP
The agent is normally
.B activated on demand
(D\-Bus / systemd) and winds itself down when idle; see
.BR "CADENCE & IDLE" .
You rarely run it by hand except for development with
.BR \-\-session .
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BR \-c ", " \-\-config " " \fIpath\fR
Path to the configuration file (default
.IR /etc/qiftop/agent.conf ).
See
.BR qiftop\-agent.conf (5).
.TP
.B \-\-session
Use the session bus instead of the system bus. Development only.
.TP
.B \-\-verbose
Enable verbose tracing on stderr.
.TP
.BR \-h ", " \-\-help ", " \-v ", " \-\-version
Show help / version and exit.
.SH D-BUS INTERFACE
Well\-known name:
.BR org.qiftop.NetworkAgent1 .
.TP
.B /org/qiftop/NetworkAgent1/Interfaces
Interface:
.BR org.qiftop.NetworkAgent1.Interfaces :
methods
.BR GetInterfaces() ", " SetDesiredIntervalMs(u) ;
signals
.BR StatsChanged ", " CadenceChanged ;
properties
.BR Version ", " Capabilities .
.TP
.B /org/qiftop/NetworkAgent1/Connections
Interface:
.BR org.qiftop.NetworkAgent1.Connections :
methods
.BR GetConnections() ", " GetProcessDetails(u) ", " SetDesiredIntervalMs(u) ;
signals
.BR ConnectionsChanged ", " PermissionDenied ", " AccountingChanged .
.SH SECURITY
.SS Access control
The system\-bus policy
.RI ( org.qiftop.NetworkAgent1.conf )
restricts all method calls and signal reception to members of the
.B netdev
group. This protects the conntrack table (normally root\-only) and prevents
cadence\-hint abuse. The Debian/RPM
.B postinst
ensures the group exists and adds the installing user. Log out and back in
or run
.BR "newgrp netdev"
for membership to take effect. Clients that lack access fall back cleanly
to their in\-process backend.
.SS Capabilities
The packaged systemd unit grants
.BR CAP_NET_ADMIN ", " CAP_SYS_PTRACE ", " CAP_DAC_READ_SEARCH ", and " CAP_SYS_ADMIN
for network capture and attribution. It also runs with systemd hardening,
including
.BR NoNewPrivileges .
.SS Process\-detail disclosure
.BR GetProcessDetails (pid)
returns basic process fields
.RB ( pid ", " uid ", " comm ", " "start time" )
to any netdev caller. The more sensitive
.IR exe ", " cwd " and " cmdline
fields are gated by the
.B [process_details] disclosure
policy (default:
.BR owner " \(em root or the process owner only)."
See
.BR qiftop\-agent.conf (5).
.SH CADENCE & IDLE
The agent polls at a base cadence and accepts client hints via
.BR SetDesiredIntervalMs(u) ,
using the minimum live hint, clamped to a configured floor. Hints expire
after a TTL. With no method calls for the idle timeout the agent pauses
polling; the next call wakes it. All cadence parameters
are configurable \(em see
.BR qiftop\-agent.conf (5).
.SH ACTIVATION
.PP
When installed via the
.B qiftop\-agent
package, the daemon is D\-Bus\-activatable and ships a systemd unit. To
manage it manually:
.PP
.RS 4
.nf
sudo systemctl daemon\-reload
sudo systemctl start qiftop\-agent
.fi
.RE
.SH VERIFICATION
Confirm the agent is reachable and serving data:
.PP
.RS 4
.nf
busctl \-\-system call org.qiftop.NetworkAgent1 \\
    /org/qiftop/NetworkAgent1/Interfaces \\
    org.qiftop.NetworkAgent1.Interfaces GetInterfaces
.fi
.RE
.PP
.B GetConnections
returns the last emitted snapshot, refreshed on a poll tick. Send a
.B SetDesiredIntervalMs
hint and wait one tick before reading if you need a fresh capture.
.SH FILES
.TP
.I /etc/qiftop/agent.conf
Configuration (conffile; preserved across upgrades). See
.BR qiftop\-agent.conf (5).
.TP
.I /usr/share/dbus\-1/system.d/org.qiftop.NetworkAgent1.conf
System\-bus access policy (netdev gate).
.TP
.I /lib/systemd/system/qiftop\-agent.service
systemd unit (capabilities + sandbox).
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR qiftop\-agent.conf (5),
.BR qiftop (1),
.BR nqiftop (1),
.BR busctl (1),
.BR systemctl (1),
.BR capabilities (7)
